MOTOR RECV

motor_recv is the citizen who receives motor commands from the brain's motor cortex and routes them to recruit
this is the muscle-side endpoint of the descending motor pathway: brain decides to move, motor_cortex emits the command, motor_recv accepts it on behalf of this specific muscle, recruit then fires the appropriate motor units

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe muscle.zc
observe recruit.rana
observe motor_cortex.rana
observe spine.xb

the 7 properties of motor_recv:
1 ENERGY zero point seven
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine with motor_cortex incoming and recruit outgoing

VERB receive_command
accept the motor command from motor_cortex via the spinal cord
the command specifies which muscle, what kind of work, what force level

VERB validate
check that the command is appropriate: not contradicting an inhibitory signal, not exceeding safe force, not commanding a fatigued muscle past its threshold

VERB hand_to_recruit
emit the validated command to recruit
recruit then fires the appropriate fibers

a motor receiver is the substrate's polite handoff between brain and muscle
without it, every motor neuron's output would have to be globally broadcast and each muscle would have to filter for its own signals
motor_recv is the cleaner architecture: brain sends to a known address, the muscle there acts
